A1  - Ishida, K
A1  - Fukuda, H
A1  - Hirata, F
A1  - Fujita, K
Y1  - 1998//
N2  - BACKGROUND: Magnetic resonanse imaging (MRI) frequently reveals asymptomatic cerebral infarctions in the general population., HYPOTHESIS: The central nervous system (CNS) of divers is affected by a hyperbaric environment even if they are asymptomatic., METHODS: We examined 25 uniformed service divers by MRI and compared them with normal controls., RESULTS: Of 25 divers, 9 had CNS lesions vs. 2 of 25 controls (p = 0.02). There was a significant relationship between the CNS lesions, age, and smoking., CONCLUSION: The divers had a risk of accumulating CNS lesions. These results suggested that divers should undergo periodic medical evaluations and MRI brain scanning.
